{
  "_comment": "External threat-intel for IP artifacts. One doc per IP, keyed by source.ip / artifact.value (same value). Written by `dshield_prism intel refresh`. Provider-specific raw responses live under providers.<name>.raw (disabled-index); structured fields under providers.<name>.structured. The derived block is recomputed every refresh and is what the rest of the pipeline reads. The `providers` object uses dynamic=strict so a provider block written without an explicit mapping declaration fails loudly at write time — prevents the M2 footgun where greynoise/abuseipdb fields got auto-inferred as text+keyword before our explicit mapping landed, then refused all subsequent type changes. Adding a new provider must update this mapping FIRST, then deploy code. NOTE: only top-level `_comment` keys are stripped by the loader; do NOT add `_comment` inside nested property bodies (ES rejects as `unsupported parameter`).",
  "settings": {
    "number_of_shards": 1,
    "number_of_replicas": 0,
    "refresh_interval": "30s"
  },
  "mappings": {
    "dynamic": "strict",
    "properties": {
      "artifact": {
        "properties": {
          "kind": {
            "type": "keyword"
          },
          "value": {
            "type": "keyword"
          },
          "first_observed_locally": {
            "type": "date"
          }
        }
      },
      "last_refreshed": {
        "type": "date"
      },
      "providers": {
        "type": "object",
        "dynamic": "strict",
